Hi,

A new question for a new situation.  My 30-year wonderful marriage to
a wonderful
man has been abruptly gone haywire.  My husband swears that he is
devoted and
loves me dearly, but as of five years ago, he worked daily with what
he calls his *soulmate*,
*the most beautiful woman in the world*, and *his very best friend*.
On my last birthday
he slept in the same apartment with her (not ours), and this coming
Christmas holidays
he is leaving to travel 3,000 miles to see her (and her husband),
dumping me with my
children alone.  Since that collaboration with her, he has ignored me,
criticized and
become a completely different person.  To his credit, he has dropped
all his medication
for the serious Major Clinical Depression (because she told him to)
and this has
been the ONLY major bone of contention between us-- that he should
take his meds
as his dr. has advised, and as he has tried to commit suicide without
them.

He wants me to believe that this is just a friend, and told my doctor
I was schizophrenic
and needed new drugs.  He says I am delusionally jealous. Maybe he's
trying to put me in mental hospital.  I am fine,
just pissed an heart-broken.  I have recommended a separation until he
gets
his head straight, and my doctor agrees that is a good idea.

So, here is the question: What is the problem, completely withdrawing
from
antidepressants and losing 80 pounds, and his mind, or &quot;true love&quot;?
Maybe
both?  I have not idea what direction this is going to take, or WHY
the doctor
allowed this, for heaven's sake.

Thanks for reading.  The withdrawal took a year, and he is just
getting
worse.  I am heart-broken.  But I will not allow this ****** to take a
place
in my house, physically on the daily-basis e-mails they have.

Thanks
