It sounds to me like your husband is checking out of your marriage.
If that is _really_ what he wants, you can't stop him.  Your choices
are relatively few here, but there are two things you could do:

- offer him the choice of going to joint counseling with you if he has
any interest in working with you to repair your marriage.

- I don't know to what extent you do things for him, or help him with
the rest of life, etc., but don't let him &quot;have his cake and eat it
too.&quot;  That is, make it clear that unless he is willing to recommit
to your marriage, you don't want him around and don't want to be
doing things for him.

The goal of this second thing isn't to punish - it is to try to make
sure he understands the consequences for him of refusing to commit to
his marriage.
