stop the suspicious nagging.&quot;.  I don't even know what that means.
Does it mean that it's a real possibility?  Does it mean that you've
completely imagined it as a possibility?  Does it mean that you
imagined that he's tried it?  Does it mean that you've been told that
you're imagining it, but that you think it's possible?  Does it mean
that you've been told that you're imagining that he's actually tried
it?

Maybe you aren't clear in expressing what you mean because you don't
really know what you mean.  If so, I think you really do have to think
these things through.  I also think this lack of clarity is exhibited
in the list of things you want from your DH.  If that's not the case,
then I'm not sure that list is conducive to a strong marriage.  At
least it would not be for me.
